                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.73/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-16T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 16, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 16—9:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1156. Department’s instruction 1337, September 4th<note n="4" xml:id="d859fn4"
                        >Not printed.</note> and Legation’s telegram Number 998, November 14th, 5
                    p.m. Following from Kuo Wen News Agency featured local press of December 14:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Nanking telegram saying [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] the Minister of
                            Communications has decided to notify the Eastern Cable Company that its
                            agreement with the Chinese Government, which expires the end of next
                            year, will not be renewed in its present form. A communication to this
                            effect will be delivered to the company on or before December 20th.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
